info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 21 at 9:09PM CDT until April 23 at 1:00PM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Minnesota... Prairie River near Taconite affecting Itasca County. Snake River near Pine City affecting Pine County. Mississippi River at Fort Ripley affecting Morrison and Crow Wing Counties. Mississippi River At Aitkin affecting Crow Wing and Aitkin Counties. ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL EARLY SUNDAY AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and remains forecast. * WHERE...Snake River near Pine City. * WHEN...Until early Sunday afternoon. * IMPACTS...At 9.0 feet, This will cause flooding near Cross Lake near Pine City. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 8:15 PM CDT Friday the stage was 9.1 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 8:15 PM CDT Friday was 9.3 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage Sunday morning. - Flood stage is 9.0 feet. - Flood safety information can be found at www.weather.gov/safety/flood. && Fld Observed Forecasts (7 pm CDT) Location Stg Stg Day/Time Sat Sun Mon Snake River Pine City 9.0 9.1 Fri 8 pm CDT 9.0 8.9 8.7 &&
info.instruction: Report observed flooding to local emergency services or law enforcement and to the National Weather Service in Duluth when you can do so safely. Flooding can be reported to the National Weather Service at 1-800-685-8612. Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov/duluth. The next statement will be issued Saturday evening by 1100 PM CDT.
